The paper deals with automated tumor detection using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of weakly supervised learning and feature pyramid networks also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the use of medical imaging data indicates a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
